The article discusses the nomination of Sarah Bloom Raskin as Vice Chair for Supervision at the Federal Reserve. Raskin, who has extensive experience in finance and cybersecurity, received broad support for her nomination. However, she faced baseless attacks from industry and conservative interest groups. The article criticizes Senate Republicans for prioritizing these attacks over addressing inflation and lowering costs for the American people. The article also urges the Senate Banking Committee to confirm four other qualified nominees for the Board of Governors.